We have developed a new module called "Authoritative Sources (CUBE) - Mapping Attestation." This module will automatically generate a record for each affected regional segment whenever there is a material change to a citation. Only the Regulatory Content Mapper responsible for that regional segment will have the authority to perform the attestation. The name of the attestor and the date of attestation will be stored automatically.

Please note that the count displayed on the dashboard will indicate only the number of citations requiring attestation, not the total number of attestation records.

If an attestation is pending and a subsequent material change occurs, the system will not generate a new attestation record for that specific regional segment.

The attestation record will be canceled if the citation is no longer active, no longer requires mapping, or if there are changes to the affected regional segments.

**Potential Enhancements:**

- When there is a change in segments, only request attestation for the new segments.
- Store a snapshot of the attested values on the attestation form.
